The paper discusses a method for causal discovery based on the additive noise model and justifies it using algorithmic information theory. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), information theory (cs.IT), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and social and information networks (cs.SI).
